---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Static page generated automatically from HTML
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy · MASSKA Festival"
  description="Cookies and localStorage policy for MASSKA Festival website."
  lang="en"
  showPartners={false}
  redirectToPreferredLanguage={true}
>
<section class="page-section">
            <div class="section-inner">
                <h1>Cookie and localStorage Policy</h1>
                <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> October 27, 2025</p>

                <h2>1. What are cookies and localStorage?</h2>
                <p>Cookies are small text files stored in your web browser when you visit websites. LocalStorage is a
                    browser mechanism that allows local data storage without an expiration date.</p>
                <p>Our website uses <strong>localStorage</strong> to remember user preferences and
                    <strong>Google Analytics cookies</strong> to analyze website traffic.
                </p>

                <h2>2. What data do we store?</h2>

                <h3>2.1. LocalStorage (functional data)</h3>
                <p>We store the following information in localStorage:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Text size</strong> – Your font zoom settings (from 0.9 to 1.3)</li>
                    <li><strong>High contrast mode</strong> – Whether you've enabled high contrast</li>
                    <li><strong>Preferred language</strong> – Choice between Polish and English version</li>
                    <li><strong>Cookie consent</strong> – Information about accepting the informational banner</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>2.2. Google Analytics (analytical cookies)</h3>
                <p>Google Analytics (ID: G-CKB0FYJDGK) stores the following data:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>_ga</strong> – user identifier (validity: 2 years)</li>
                    <li><strong>_ga_*</strong> – session state and campaign parameters (validity: 2 years)</li>
                    <li><strong>Behavioral data</strong> – pages visited, visit duration, traffic source</li>
                    <li><strong>Technical data</strong> – browser type, operating system, screen resolution</li>
                    <li><strong>IP address</strong> – anonymized (last octet masked)</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Google Analytics DOES NOT collect</strong> personal data such as name, surname, email, or
                    address.</p>

                <h3>2.3. Google Maps (media cookies)</h3>
                <p>Embedded Google Maps may set their own cookies and process device data:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>NID</strong> – Google preferences identifier (up to 6 months)</li>
                    <li><strong>1P_JAR, CONSENT</strong> – Google privacy and consent settings</li>
                    <li><strong>Location data</strong> – geographic coordinates of displayed location</li>
                    <li><strong>Technical data</strong> – browser type, screen resolution</li>
                </ul>
                <p>More info: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google
                        Privacy Policy</a></p>

                <h3>2.4. YouTube video (media cookies)</h3>
                <p>Videos may be embedded from YouTube using <strong>privacy‑enhanced mode</strong>
                    (<code>youtube-nocookie.com</code>). When you click the load button or consent to media,
                    YouTube may set its own cookies and process device data.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>YSC</strong> – playback session identifier (session)</li>
                    <li><strong>VISITOR_INFO1_LIVE</strong> – bandwidth measurement/player config (up to 6 months)</li>
                    <li><strong>PREF</strong> – playback preferences (up to 8 months)</li>
                    <li><strong>CONSENT</strong> – Google consent status</li>
                </ul>
                <p>More info: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google
                        Privacy Policy</a>,
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/t/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube Terms of
                        Service</a>.
                </p>

                <h2>3. Purpose of processing</h2>

                <h3>3.1. LocalStorage</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Ensuring website accessibility for people with disabilities</li>
                    <li>Remembering your display preferences during subsequent visits</li>
                    <li>Improving website usability by preserving language settings</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>3.2. Google Analytics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Analyzing website traffic and user behavior</li>
                    <li>Identifying popular content and improving site structure</li>
                    <li>Optimizing accessibility and usability</li>
                    <li>Creating festival viewership statistics</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>3.3. Google Maps</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Displaying interactive map with festival location (Mamuszki 14, Sopot)</li>
                    <li>Enabling easy navigation to the event venue</li>
                    <li>Providing precise geographic information</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>3.4. YouTube</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Displaying promotional video content</li>
                    <li>Providing video playback functionality</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>4. Legal basis</h2>
                <p>Data processing is based on:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>GDPR Art. 6(1)(a)</strong> – User consent expressed by clicking the "Understood" button
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>GDPR Art. 6(1)(f)</strong> – Legitimate interest of the controller in ensuring
                        functionality and analyzing the website</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>5. Storage period</h2>

                <h3>5.1. LocalStorage</h3>
                <p>Data in localStorage is stored <strong>indefinitely</strong>, until:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>The user clears browser data</li>
                    <li>Data is deleted via browser function</li>
                    <li>Browser reinstallation</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>5.2. Google Analytics</h3>
                <p>Google Analytics cookies are stored for <strong>24 months</strong> from last activity.</p>

                <h2>6. Data sharing</h2>
                <p><strong>LocalStorage:</strong> Data is not sent to servers or shared with third parties.</p>
                <p><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> Data is processed by Google LLC in the USA based on:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC) approved by the European Commission</li>
                    <li>Google Privacy Policy: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a></li>
                    <li>Google Analytics Terms of Service</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>IP Anonymization:</strong> All IP addresses are anonymized before processing.</p>

                <h2>7. Opting out of Google Analytics</h2>
                <p>You can opt out of Google Analytics tracking in several ways:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Browser add-on:</strong> Install <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout"
                            target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a></li>
                    <li><strong>Block cookies:</strong> Disable analytical cookies in browser settings</li>
                    <li><strong>Private mode:</strong> Use incognito/private browsing mode</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>8. How to manage localStorage and cookies?</h2>
                <p>You can delete localStorage data at any time:</p>

                <h3>Chrome/Edge:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data</li>
                    <li>See all site data and permissions</li>
                    <li>Search for "masska" or domain name</li>
                    <li>Click the trash icon to delete data</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Firefox:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Options → Privacy & Security</li>
                    <li>Cookies and Site Data → Manage Data</li>
                    <li>Search for "masska"</li>
                    <li>Remove Selected</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Safari:</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
                    <li>Search for "masska"</li>
                    <li>Remove</li>
                </ol>

                <h2>9. Your rights</h2>
                <p>Under GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Right of access</strong> to your data (you can check it in the browser's developer
                        console: localStorage)</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to deletion</strong> of data (clear localStorage in browser)</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to object</strong> to processing (disable localStorage in browser settings)</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to lodge a complaint</strong> with the supervisory authority</li>
                </ul>

                <h2>10. Data controller</h2>
                <p>The data controller is:</p>
                <p><strong>Na Drodze Ekspresji Association</strong><br>
                    <a href="https://ekspresja.org">https://ekspresja.org</a><br>
                    For data protection matters, please use the <a href="contact.html">contact form</a>.
                </p>

                <h2>11. Policy changes</h2>
                <p>We reserve the right to make changes to this policy. We will inform about any changes by updating
                    the date at the top of the document.</p>

                <h2>12. Contact</h2>
                <p>For questions regarding the cookie policy, please use the <a href="contact.html">contact form</a>.
                </p>

                <hr style="margin: 3rem 0; border: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);">

                <h2>13. Consents and external media (YouTube, Google Maps)</h2>
                <p>YouTube videos are <strong>blocked by default</strong>. You can:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Load a single video via the "Load video" button in the embed placeholder</li>
                    <li>Give persistent consent to media with the "Always allow media" button</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Google Maps are loaded automatically</strong> and use cookies described in section 2.3.</p>
                <p>To reset media consent and see the block again:</p>
                <button class="button secondary" type="button" data-action="reset-media-consent">Reset media
                    consent</button>

                <div class="cookie-notice" data-consent-banner role="dialog" aria-live="polite" hidden
                    style="margin-top: 2rem;">
                    <img src="../assets/img/cookie.webp" alt="" width="48" height="48" loading="lazy"
                        decoding="async" />
                    <div class="cookie-notice__content">
                        <p>We use analytics (Google Analytics), maps (Google Maps) and external media (YouTube). Adjust
                            your preferences
                            below.</p>
                        <details class="cookie-notice__settings">
                            <summary>Settings</summary>
                            <fieldset>
                                <legend class="sr-only">Consent preferences</legend>
                                <label><input type="checkbox" data-consent-toggle="analytics"> Analytics (Google
                                    Analytics)</label>
                                <label><input type="checkbox" data-consent-toggle="media"> Media (YouTube
                                    embeds)</label>
                            </fieldset>
                            <div class="cookie-notice__actions-row">
                                <button type="button" class="button" data-consent-save>Save choices</button>
                            </div>
                        </details>
                    </div>
                    <div class="cookie-notice__actions">
                        <button type="button" class="cookie-notice__button" data-consent-accept-all>Accept all</button>
                        <button type="button" class="cookie-notice__button ghost" data-consent-reject>Reject
                            non‑essential</button>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Summary for users</h2>
                <div class="info-panel" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
                    <p><strong>In short:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>We use localStorage (preferences), Google Analytics (statistics) and Google Maps (maps)</li>
                        <li>LocalStorage: we only save your display settings (contrast, font, language)</li>
                        <li>Google Analytics: anonymous visit statistics (no personal data)</li>
                        <li>Google Maps: interactive maps with festival location</li>
                        <li>You can disable Google Analytics with a browser add-on</li>
                        <li>LocalStorage data stays in your browser only</li>
                        <li>By accepting the banner, you agree to all mechanisms</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
</BaseLayout>
